# $Header: $

  25 May 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> sunos/package.mask:
  Mask portage-2.1.27.6600 on Solaris as pty is non-existant there

  04 May 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> linux/x86/package.mask:
  Remove mask for openssl on x86, the cause has been found and a fix checked in

  30 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> sunos/package.mask:
  Mask emacs-cvs-23.0.0-r6 on Solaris because it doesn't compile

  20 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> linux/make.defaults:
  Drop fortran USE flag in linux profile

  20 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> make.defaults:
  Drop berkdb USE flag, and add ssl as a default. Added little description on
  why

  18 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> +linux/x86/package.mask:
  Mask dev-libs/openssl-0.9.8e on x86, see
  http://article.gmane.org/gmane.linux.gentoo.alt/2351

  14 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  darwin/macos/10.3/package.mask:
  Masked odcctools-20070412 because also that one fails

  12 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> +darwin/macos/packages,
  darwin/macos/virtuals, virtuals:
  Say bye bye to virtual/gcc.  It was a not so good idea.

  12 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> aix/packages,
  +darwin/macos/package.mask:
  Add deb2targz as system package for AIX, because it's necessary to unpack
  .deb files (ca-certificates). Mask gcc for Mac OS X profiles, because only
  gcc-apple is really supported there

  10 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> make.defaults:
  Add ncurses to the default USE list

  09 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> packages:
  Don't require virtual/libc and virtual/os-headers to be installed, we won't
  ever install them, will we?

  06 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> +make.defaults:
  Add some USE defaults in make.default

  06 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> use.force:
  Force "prefix" flag to be set, allows to do "prefix? ( ) "-like constucts

  06 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> linux/use.mask,
  +use.force, use.mask:
  Unforce linux/glibc use-expanded flags forced in the base profile

  05 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> +aix/packages,
  darwin/macos/make.defaults, +irix/packages, linux/packages, packages,
  +sunos/packages:
  Mask binutils from the base profile, and add binutils, odcctools,
  native-cctools in the sub-profiles

  05 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> aix/make.defaults,
  darwin/make.defaults, irix/make.defaults, linux/make.defaults,
  +package.provided, sunos/make.defaults:
  Add nostip to non-Linux profiles because they don't have scanelf. Added
  package.provided for sys-apps/shadow.

  04 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> aix/use.mask,
  darwin/use.mask, sunos/use.mask, +use.mask:
  Moved elibc/kernel/userland USE-flags masking to the default-prefix profile,
  and unmasked them in the specific profiles again

  04 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>:
  Depend on the base profile, just only change the defaults when required

